8. Anti-Corruption Guidelines 8.1 The Supplier shall:

In this Agreement, the Supplier acknowledges its commitment to upholding the highest ethical standards regarding anti-corruption practices. To that end, the Supplier will:

a) Ensure that no employee, agent, or affiliate engages in any form of corrupt practice, including bribery, extortion, or embezzlement, either directly or indirectly, while performing duties associated with this Agreement;

b) Maintain and enforce policies, procedures, and controls designed to prevent, detect, and remediate instances of corruption and ensure compliance with all applicable anti-corruption laws and regulations in every jurisdiction where it operates;

c) Cooperate fully with the Principal and any competent authorities in investigating any allegations or suspected violations of anti-corruption laws and regulations in connection with this Agreement;

d) Provide the Principal with relevant information and documentation upon request, to enable the Principal to monitor and verify compliance with these Anti-Corruption Guidelines.

This clause is intended to create a shared responsibility between the Supplier and the Principal for upholding anti-corruption standards. Any failure to meet these requirements may lead to termination of this Agreement and potential legal consequences.
